&ldquo;More than&rdquo; vs. &ldquo;Of&rdquo; Definitions:
 Using &ldquo;of&rdquo;
In a class, there are 30 students. By the policy of the university, 10% of the class will get &lsquo;A&rsquo; grades. How many people would get &lsquo;A&rsquo; at the end of the semester?
 Using &ldquo;more than&rdquo;
Issac runs an ice cream store and today he got 100 customers. He wants to forecast the number of tomorrow&rsquo;s customers using statistical method. After the study, he predicts that the number of the customers will be 50% more than today&rsquo;s customer.
